    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-05T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-05T03:00:00-05:00" n="987"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d987">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 LCC/7–544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-05T11:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 5, 1944—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2423. Embassy’s 2236, June 22, 10 p.m. The Foreign Office states in a note dated
                    July 1 that the following delegation to the London Committee on Political
                    Propaganda has been appointed by the Soviet Government: Chairman of the
                    Delegation, A. A. Sobolev, Counselor of the Soviet Embassy in Great Britain, G.
                    F. Saksin, Counselor of the Soviet Embassy in Great Britain, and Major General
                    A. V. Vasilev, Deputy Head of the Soviet military mission in London.</p>
                <p>The Foreign Office also states that a special “Bureau of Propaganda for Enemy and
                    Enemy-occupied Countries” has been organized in the Sovinformburo headed by S.
                    A. Lozovski who may be approached in regard to all pertinent questions.</p>
                <p>Sent Department repeated London as 125.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
